<TITLE> Escaped inmate who cheated David Letterman nabbed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 HELENA, Montana, June (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Two Montana State Prison escapees, including a man accused of plotting to kidnap David Letterman's son two years ago, were captured on Wednesday in wooded areas in northwestern Montana, authorities said. Officials said they nabbed Kelly Frank, 45, and William Willcutt, 22, hours apart at two separate locations, five days after the men had escaped from the state prison some 175 miles away. "We're back in a position where we feel that public safety has been restored," said State Prison Warden Mike Mahoney. Frank was serving a 10-year prison term for felony theft for overcharging Letterman while working as a painter on the television personality's ranch near Choteau, Montana. He was arrested in 2005 on accusations that he planned to kidnap Harry Letterman and the boy's nanny for a $5 million ransom. A kidnapping charge was dropped in exchange for his guilty plea to other charges, including the the
